The Inspector General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, on Friday ordered the immediate redeployment of the Commissioner ofÂ Police in Rivers State, Mustapha Dandaura, replacing CP with Joseph Mukan.
CP Mustapha Dandaura has been redeployed to the Provost FHQ, Abuja.
A statement by the Force Public Relation Officer, Frank Mba. on Friday indicated that the IGP also approved the redeployment of CP Musa Adze, CP Anti-Fraud Unit.
The statement further indicated that the IGP charged the affected Commissioners of Police to diligently and professionally discharge their duties in their new areas of responsibilities.
The posting and the redeployment of the affected Senior Police Officers is with immediate effect, Mba said.

			
